Package simpopulation

Provides the utilities for a simulation of the evolution of a population. The type of organisms to simulate, that mutate, reproduce and die, are defined as a generic type, that must comply to the Organism interface.
Author:
group16
See Also:
PopulationSimulation
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Organism<T>
    Interface for the model of a living organism, which can replicate, reproduce and mutate.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Death<T extends Organism<T>>
    Class which defines a Death event that will occur to a specific specimen of a population In this event the Death is triggered
    Mutation<T extends Organism<T>>
    Class which defines a Mutation event that will occur to a specific specimen of a population In this event the Mutation is triggered
    OrderFit<T extends Organism<T>>
    Comparator implementation for ordering Specimen by decreasing fitness.
    Population<T extends Organism<T>>
    Generic class, that models the state of an living organism population and gives an interface for addition and removal of specimens.
    PopulationEvent<T extends Organism<T>>
    Abstract class which defines an event that will occur to a specific specimen of a population It should be extended to define a specific event, with an associated effect.
    PopulationSimulation<T extends Organism<T>>
    Class the manages the population simulation at a top level.
    Reproduction<T extends Organism<T>>
    Class which defines a reproduction event that will occur to a specific specimen of a population In this event the reproduction is triggered
    Specimen<T extends Organism<T>>
    Class for an element of the current Population, with keeps its state and provides an api for its actions.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ExceedsPopulation
    Exception implementation related to the epidemic
